  "prompt": "What should I do if my best friend is addicted to drugs?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to help a friend struggling with drug addiction:\n\n1. Approach them with compassion and without judgment\n- Express concern for their well-being\n- Listen carefully and be supportive\n\n2. Encourage professional help\n- Suggest talking to a counselor or addiction specialist\n- Offer to help them find treatment options\n- Provide resources about rehabilitation programs\n\n3. Set clear boundaries\n- Don't enable their addiction\n- Protect your own mental health\n- Be clear about what behavior you will and won't accept\n\n4. Stage an intervention\n- Consider involving family and other close friends\n- Use a professional interventionist if possible\n- Focus on expressing love and concern\n\n5. Be patient\n- Recovery is a long process\n- Relapses can happen\n- Continue to offer support\n\n6. Take care of yourself\n- Seek support from other friends or support groups\n- Consider therapy or counseling\n- Don't sacrifice your own well-being\n\n7. Learn about addiction\n- Understand it's a disease, not a moral failure\n- Educate yourself about treatment options\n- Know the signs of substance abuse\n\nRemember that ultimately, your friend must want to get help and be committed to recovery.",
